comments.content: The selenium-centred micronutrient biological network. The most relevant biochemical processes related to selenium in the context of metabolism, oxidation and inflammation are represented. Also, the compartmental separation (intracellular vs. plasma) is presented, identifying the selenium centred plasma metabolome. A selenoprotein database exists at: http://www.selenodb.org
This pathway was inferred from Homo sapiens pathway [http://wikipathways.org/instance/WP15_r96318 WP15_96318] with a 81.0% conversion rate.
